      "width": 346.2292175292969,
      "height": 240,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b12",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 192760807,
      "version": 468,
      "versionNonce": 1532899943,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775192465564,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. This architectural design ensures that the\nLast-Level Cache (LLC/L3) acts as a central\nrepository containing copies of all data stored\nin the smaller, private L1 and L2 caches of\nevery individual core.\n\n2. Global Invalidation: Because of the\ninclusivity rule, when the clflush instruction\nevicts a memory line from the LLC, the\nhardware automatically removes that same\ndata from every other cache level in the entire\nprocessor hierarchy.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. This architectural design ensures that the Last-Level Cache (LLC/L3) acts as a central repository containing copies of all data stored in the smaller, private L1 and L2 caches of every individual core.\n\n2. Global Invalidation: Because of the inclusivity rule, when the clflush instruction evicts a memory line from the LLC, the hardware automatically removes that same data from every other cache level in the entire processor hierarchy.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
