      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775192460047,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "J4PV8hWIwvH-wYR4YGL7W",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1313.267390659877,
      "y": 2616.544771103632,
      "width": 441.0209350585938,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b16",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2071763143,
      "version": 639,
      "versionNonce": 1038546569,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "mwJCczoF_gYThIw1NFdL1",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1775192567351,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. The availability of a high-resolution timer, specifically the\nrdtsc (Read Time-Stamp Counter) instruction is another\nprerequisite.\n\n2. Cycle Counting: The rdtsc instruction reads a 64-bit\ncounter that increments with every clock cycle. By taking a\ntimestamp before and after a memory access, the spy\ncalculates the exact number of CPU cycles the operation\ntook.\n\n3. Establishing Thresholds: This high resolution allows the\nattacker to establish a system-specific threshold (e.g., 120\ncycles). If the rdtsc difference is below this threshold, it is\nidentified as a cache hit (indicating victim access); if it is\nsignificantly higher (e.g., 200–300+ cycles), it is a cache miss",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. The availability of a high-resolution timer, specifically the rdtsc (Read Time-Stamp Counter) instruction is another prerequisite.\n\n2. Cycle Counting: The rdtsc instruction reads a 64-bit counter that increments with every clock cycle. By taking a timestamp before and after a memory access, the spy calculates the exact number of CPU cycles the operation took.\n\n3. Establishing Thresholds: This high resolution allows the attacker to establish a system-specific threshold (e.g., 120 cycles). If the rdtsc difference is below this threshold, it is identified as a cache hit (indicating victim access); if it is significantly higher (e.g., 200–300+ cycles), it is a cache miss",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
