    },
    {
      "id": "jGu3YPC-7l6hhJ8vJuKkr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1962.5902818952286,
      "y": 2644.357347397577,
      "width": 395.8125000000002,
      "height": 260,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1A",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1603559879,
      "version": 559,
      "versionNonce": 1048027751,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775192449148,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Executing on the same physical processor is\nanother prerequisite.\n\n2. The attack targets the Last-Level Cache (LLC),\nwhich is a resource shared by multiple cores on a\nsingle processor die.\n\n3. Physical die boundaries: Because the LLC is internal\nto the physical processor, a spy cannot monitor a\nvictim if they are executing on two different physical\nCPU sockets, as they would not share an L3 cache.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Executing on the same physical processor is another prerequisite.\n\n2. The attack targets the Last-Level Cache (LLC), which is a resource shared by multiple cores on a single processor die.\n\n3. Physical die boundaries: Because the LLC is internal to the physical processor, a spy cannot monitor a victim if they are executing on two different physical CPU sockets, as they would not share an L3 cache.\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
