    {
      "id": "bJQkiagWUGcic1jeqK9bL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 341.17367335728215,
      "y": 3932.8245366414385,
      "width": 584.0428466796874,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1O",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 605754535,
      "version": 251,
      "versionNonce": 496821033,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775193026737,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Flush serves as the critical \"reset\" step that prepares\nthe processor's cache for monitoring.\n\n2. Ensures that a specific, monitored memory line is completely\nabsent from the cache hierarchy before the victim process has a\nchance to execute.\n\n3. Using cflush instruction, the spy removes the memory line\nfrom the L3 cache, leading to the removal from all other caches.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Flush serves as the critical \"reset\" step that prepares\nthe processor's cache for monitoring.\n\n2. Ensures that a specific, monitored memory line is completely absent from the cache hierarchy before the victim process has a chance to execute.\n\n3. Using cflush instruction, the spy removes the memory line from the L3 cache, leading to the removal from all other caches.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "yYQ16xTEJuNhV2KCHjUd1",
