      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "_XsJz-yJKsM79YXmNkf-N",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1046.7712685721262,
      "y": 3925.681679498581,
      "width": 624.0428466796875,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1T",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 441972839,
      "version": 385,
      "versionNonce": 349991305,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775193158684,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. The wait phase is essentially a period of passive observation. \n\n2. Capturing Activity: If the victim accesses the memory line during\nthis phase, the line is brought back into the cache from main memory.\n\n3. Implementation: In the authors' implementation, the spy program\ndivides time into fixed slots of 2,500 cycles. After flushing the\nmonitored lines, the spy program performs a busy wait until the end\nof the current time slot before initiating the reload phase.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. The wait phase is essentially a period of passive observation. \n\n2. Capturing Activity: If the victim accesses the memory line during this phase, the line is brought back into the cache from main memory.\n\n3. Implementation: In the authors' implementation, the spy program divides time into fixed slots of 2,500 cycles. After flushing the monitored lines, the spy program performs a busy wait until the end of the current time slot before initiating the reload phase.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "664xAQFhrUs5kcn3T33m1",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1788.7928662981305,
      "y": 3889.8482008434476,
      "width": 936.666608537946,
      "height": 286.66678292410734,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1U",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 599212263,
      "version": 303,
      "versionNonce": 813321735,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "licKIBk7C5FLAAnWB8XPV",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1775193534927,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "4Z3NRvSHFz3HfR0S6fFAz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1821.7711813790456,
      "y": 3915.681592305501,
      "width": 876.5426722935268,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1V",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1807389223,
      "version": 630,
      "versionNonce": 96245449,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775193445417,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Reload is the data-collection stage where the spy process extracts information by measuring\nhow long it takes to read a monitored memory line. \n\n2. Measurement: The spy uses the rdtsc instruction to read the processor's 64-bit time stamp\ncounter before and after accessing the memory location. By subtracting the initial value from the\nfinal value, the spy calculates the exact number of CPU cycles the read operation required.\n\n3. Cache Hit: Cycle count < 120\n\n4. Cache Miss: Cycle count (200-300)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Reload is the data-collection stage where the spy process extracts information by measuring how long it takes to read a monitored memory line. \n\n2. Measurement: The spy uses the rdtsc instruction to read the processor's 64-bit time stamp counter before and after accessing the memory location. By subtracting the initial value from the final value, the spy calculates the exact number of CPU cycles the read operation required.\n\n3. Cache Hit: Cycle count < 120\n\n4. Cache Miss: Cycle count (200-300)",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
